<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11345366-jayme"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1545654456i/11345366._UX100_CR0,10,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11345366-jayme">Jayme</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Although I liked Harold Fry, I think that this book touched me so much more emotionally than Harold Fry did, BECAUSE I had read Harold Fry. It probabl<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Although I liked Harold Fry, I think that this book touched me so much more emotionally than Harold Fry did, BECAUSE I had read Harold Fry. It probably could stand alone, but I would NOT recommend it. I read the books back to back, two perspectives of the same story, and I think that is why the story is one that has stayed with me, long after the last page has been read and the last tissue crumpled.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
