<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/26491381-barbara"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1565007894i/26491381._UX100_CR0,34,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/26491381-barbara">Barbara</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I totally loved the ending on so many levels. Queenie got it all off her chest and died burden-free. Harold remained undisturbed by her revelations an<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I totally loved the ending on so many levels. Queenie got it all off her chest and died burden-free. Harold remained undisturbed by her revelations and was left with his memories intact and able to re-start life with Maureen. And that lovely nun, full of fun and wisdom....who came just to Queenie to ease her passing. I thought it was beautiful and I truly had no suspicion that that was to be the ending. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
