<div id="review_1057511845" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1057511845" />
    <a title="Joanne Harris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34428697-joanne-harris"><img alt="Joanne Harris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442439458p2/34428697.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1057511845?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joanne Harris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joanne Harris" href="/user/show/34428697-joanne-harris">Joanne Harris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385682824" href="/book/show/20890479-the-love-song-of-miss-queenie-hennessy">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1057511845" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13916092076817081903">I may be in a minority, in that I actually enjoyed this companion-piece to HAROLD FRY more than the original - perhaps because I was expecting less. Queenie&apos;s voice is well-pitched and sure; and the banality of her environment throws her rich inner life into sharp relief. There&apos;s something about this book that reminds me of some of Jane Gardam&apos;s work, especially THE QUEEN OF THE TAMBOURINE, which I love. It&apos;s touching, but not saccharine; simple, but deceptive; crammed with authentic details.</span>
  <span id="freeText13916092076817081903" style="display:none">I may be in a minority, in that I actually enjoyed this companion-piece to HAROLD FRY more than the original - perhaps because I was expecting less. Queenie's voice is well-pitched and sure; and the banality of her environment throws her rich inner life into sharp relief. There's something about this book that reminds me of some of Jane Gardam's work, especially THE QUEEN OF THE TAMBOURINE, which I love. It's touching, but not saccharine; simple, but deceptive; crammed with authentic details.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13916092076817081903" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

