        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1733209900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12428881891293329667">A companion book to The Unlikely Pilgrimage of Harold Fry tells of Queenie Hennessy&apos;s life, mainly in relation to the Harold Fry story. Set in a hospice, Queenie along with other residents are dying. Their day to day life is described. Obviously this is sometimes very sad but lovely too as you read about the residents friendships and how special and appreciated small things become. As Quennie waits for Harold she writes a letter to him explaining events from the past. I thought the twist at the </span>
  <span id="freeText12428881891293329667" style="display:none">A companion book to The Unlikely Pilgrimage of Harold Fry tells of Queenie Hennessy's life, mainly in relation to the Harold Fry story. Set in a hospice, Queenie along with other residents are dying. Their day to day life is described. Obviously this is sometimes very sad but lovely too as you read about the residents friendships and how special and appreciated small things become. As Quennie waits for Harold she writes a letter to him explaining events from the past. I thought the twist at the end was dissapointing but I enjoyed this book more than I expected.</span>
