<span id="freeTextContainer5448952649804065362">4.5 Stars<br/><br/>A quiet story of sacrifice, guilt, unrequited love, and redemption that is brilliantly told. As readers, we are privileged to journey alongside Queenie, who is slowly fading away in a hospice care home, as she waits for her dear Harold Fry to walk the length of England to see her one last time. Yep, it’s dramatic &amp; sentimental but so very worthy. I cried like a baby.<br/><br/>Reread 4/21: Bumping this one up to a full 5 Stars because Joyce is simply stunning with her language and spins such a tho</span>
  <span id="freeText5448952649804065362" style="display:none">4.5 Stars<br /><br />A quiet story of sacrifice, guilt, unrequited love, and redemption that is brilliantly told. As readers, we are privileged to journey alongside Queenie, who is slowly fading away in a hospice care home, as she waits for her dear Harold Fry to walk the length of England to see her one last time. Yep, it’s dramatic &amp; sentimental but so very worthy. I cried like a baby.<br /><br />Reread 4/21: Bumping this one up to a full 5 Stars because Joyce is simply stunning with her language and spins such a thought provoking story. A must-read companion to Harold Fry. </span>
